\begin_layout Section
Grid-Stat command line
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Grid-Stat tool in MET takes as input a configuration file (GridStat.cfg).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some MET tools like plot_data_plane and regrid_data_plane do support to
 use of configuration strings as command line arguments, but Grid-Stat is
 not one of them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Instead, the config strings should be included in the Grid-Stat configuration
 file.
 The MET User's Guide includes details about those config file options.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So a Grid-Stat command line should look like: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
grid_stat FCT.nc OBS.nc GridStat.cfg 
\end_layout

